Adds the Phase 0 orchestrator foundation alongside the existing MDO platform:

- packages/db: Drizzle ORM schema with 11 Supabase tables (agents, alerts,
  agent_actions, agent_inputs_raw, approvals, kill_state, events,
  source_quarantine, baselines, agent_runs, canary_deployments) + pgvector
  columns for future embedding pipeline. Migration, seed, and health-check scripts.

- apps/workers: TypeScript orchestrator service
  - scheduler/: node-cron reads agents table, enqueues jobs on schedule
  - orchestrator/queue.ts: BullMQ queue + worker factory
  - orchestrator/priority.ts: priority scoring (severity + freshness + IST business-hours multiplier)
  - orchestrator/dispatcher.ts: dequeues jobs, checks kill switch, loads agent module, writes run record
  - audit/logger.ts: writes every action to agent_actions (non-negotiable)
  - kill-switch/enforcer.ts: pause/resume per-agent and global; read before every run
  - replay/recorder.ts: records raw inputs to agent_inputs_raw before processing
  - replay/cli.ts: `pnpm replay --agent <id> --hours <n>` compares replay vs original outputs

- agents/_test-agent: Phase 0 hello-world agent — fires every 5 min, emits
  an alert to the alerts table, proving the full scheduler→queue→dispatch→audit pipeline

- pnpm workspaces + Turborepo wiring; CLAUDE.md with architecture + runbook

